===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|reyn}}, {{m|enm|rein}}, from {{inh|en|ang|rēn}}, {{m|ang|reġn||rain}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*regnaz||rain}} (compare West Frisian {{m|fy|rein}}, Dutch {{m|nl|regen}}, German {{m|de|Regen}}, Danish {{m|da|regn}}), from pre-Germanic {{m|ine-pro|*Hréǵ-no}}-, from {{inh|en|ine-pro|*Hreǵ}} 'to flow' (compare Latin {{m|la|rigō||wet, soak}}, Lithuanian {{m|lt|rõki||drizzling rain}}, Albanian {{m|sq|rrjedh||to flow, drip}}).

